    "Manufacturer": "General Systems",
    "Model": "",
    "UIName": "Fatman",
    "Id": "chassisdef_fatman_FTM-XX",
    "Name": "Fatman",
    "Details": "The FTM-XX is a quad superheavy originally built around autonomous operation via a head-mounted Drone Operating System, but now converted for normal MechWarrior piloting. Twin Gauss Rifles sit in each side torso with CASE protection for their ammunition. An ER PPC in the center torso provides additional long-range reach. An LRM 10 handles indirect fire. Four Small Pulse Lasers distributed across all four legs deter infantry. Ferro-Fibrous armor covers the frame. Its limited damage potential despite its humongous size makes it more of a sitting duck on a battlefield than a real threat.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Stable Weapons</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.44</color></b>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_fatman"
  },
  "VariantName": "FTM-XX",
